{
  "texts": [
    "We considered 12 different molecular property prediction tasks.",
    "To construct each task, we selected all NPs annotated with the desired property as the positive class and a random sample of NPs from CMNPD as the negative class, enforcing a minimum dataset size of 1000 compounds (Table 2).",
    "Similar dataset generation procedures have been popularized for evaluating ligand-based virtual screening approaches [24][25][26], but they have the drawback of potentially introducing noise in the labels of the inactive compounds, since the negative class is constructed by sampling unlabeled molecules.",
    "However, this was necessary for our benchmark due to the scarcity of biological annotations for NPs, making it difficult to generate classification datasets where negative data had also been measured [3,27].",
    "Molecular fingerprintsIn total, we analyzed 20 different fingerprinting algorithms belonging to five different categories (Table 3)."
  ]
}